DESCRIPTION:<p>Grief Rituals:<br>reflections on<br>migration and<br>coll
 ective mourning<br>&#10024\;<br>Rituales de duelo:<br>reflexiones sobre<
 br>la migraci&#243\;n y<br>el duelo colectivo<br><br>co-directors // nao
 mi macalalad bragin &amp\; Milvia Pacheco Salvatierra<br><br>collaborati
 ng artists // marco farroni\, Akoiya Harris\, Nia-Amina Minor\, Jasmin&#
 233\; Smith<br><br>spiritual attendant // Angela Angel<br><br>steward //
  Derek Dizon<br><br>project consultant // Ellen Sebastian Chang<br><br>S
 CHEDULE:<br>3:00pm gathering<br>3:30pm activation<br>4:30pm community di
 alogue<br><br>A Resting Place<br>670 S King Street Seattle\, WA<br><br>&
 #9889\;&#65039\;Registration&#9889\;&#65039\;Due to limited space\, we c
 an accept 21 guests. Registration closes April 10 at 12pm.<br><br><a hre
 f="http://tinyurl.com/griefrituals41226" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
 tinyurl.com/griefrituals41226</a><br><br>&#x1F49B\;Grief Rituals is a co
 mmunity ceremony honoring migration as a collective experience of loss\,
  longing and ancestral remembering. Conceived by a band of 7 artists who
  will share their migration stories through dance\, poetry\, visual art
 \, music and prayer\, the ritual process invites guests to reflect on the
  power of shared cultural history and root their healing in solidarity w
 ith others.<br><br>&#x1F49B\;This spring sharing marks our one-year anni
 versary of collaborating with Derek Dizon and A Resting Place.<br><br>&#
 x1F49B\;Little Brown Language is a Seattle-based performance group\, who
  exist to build new forms of solidarity among local artist-organizers th
 rough embodied cultural practice. We are guided by a collective commitme
 nt to healing our relations with land and lineage. We create worlds in w
 hich the hidden histories of our communities become embodied\, felt and 
 seen.<br>&#160\;</p><hr><p><br>This program is part of <em>Grief Rituals
 </em>\, a new project of Little Brown Language performance group in coll
 aboration with A Resting Place\, ARTS at King Street Station\, and Frien
 ds of the Waterfront. <em>Grief Rituals</em> will culminate with a commu
 nity ritual activation in October 2026.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Futu
 re</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, install
 ations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed 
 to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the 
 Downtown core.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/200748549
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/arts/experience/arts-events?trumba
 Embed=view%3devent%26eventid%3d200748549
END:VEVENT
