DESCRIPTION:<strong>Drums are provided. All ages. No experience necessar
 y.</strong><br><br>The Hawk Foundation for Research and Education in Afr
 ican Culture&#160\;brings master drummers to LANGSTON to engage in a wel
 l-researched pedagogy of community healing through African drumming.<br>
 <br>The Hawk Foundation is a Washington-based drum and education organiz
 ation that utilizes West African and African American music to promote e
 ducation\, team bonding\, organizational development\, and research-base
 d therapy. Through history\, Yoruba stories and classic drum rhythms\, t
 his class has reconnected students to the drum\, the past\, and themselv
 es.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
