 ps://www.trumba.com/i/DgBAQTC5zun-JdqA3%2A1orzV9.jpg" target="_blank" re
 l="noopener" title="https://www.trumba.com/i/DgBAQTC5zun-JdqA3%2A1orzV9.
 jpg">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260401T110311Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>The Drea
 ming Room: Soundscapes for Deep Rest</em>\,</strong> <strong>a concert s
 eries&#160\;hosted by Stephanie Ann Ball\, with special guest Kiesha B. 
 Free!</strong><br><br>This community-rooted concert series is designed t
 o support nervous system recovery\, emotional release\, and collective c
 onnections through sound meditation\, music\, and storytelling. Come res
 t and connect over the course of this renewing series\, every other mont
 h on the third Thursday&#160\;between February and December.<br><br><em>
 We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art 
 activations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning 
 experiences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&
 #160\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (3rd 
 Thursdays)</strong>:<br>6:00 p.m. doors\, 6:30 p.m. music</p><ul> <li>Fe
 bruary 19&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;rejuvenation + renewal	</li><li>April 16&
 #160\;&#8212\;&#160\;creativity\, fun\, expansion	</li><li>June 18&#160
 \;&#8212\;&#160\;joyful\, wondrous playtime	</li><li>August 20&#160\;&#82
 12\;&#160\;transitioning	</li><li>October 15&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;gratit
 ude + reflection	</li><li>December 17&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;celebration +
  releasing</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. 
 &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><str
 ong>Artist bios:<br><a href="https://stephanieannball.com/" target="_bla
 nk" rel="noopener">Stephanie Ann Ball</a></strong> is&#160\;a healing ar
 tist and sound meditation facilitator. Her work sits at the intersection
  of therapeutic sound\, science\, and well-being. Using sound meditation
 \, energy work\, and subconscious reprogramming techniques\, Stephanie h
 elps individuals and teams regulate the nervous system\, release stress
 \, and access states of calm\, clarity\, and flow. The best part? It all 
 starts with something easy and fun&#8212\;listening to music.<br><br><a 
 href="https://kiesha.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Kiesha
  B. Free</strong></a> is a masterful host\, speaker\, and independent cu
 ltural worker who moves through the world with heart\, humor\, and deep 
 intention.&#160\;With a background spanning tech\, media\, and performan
 ce\, she brings people together across differences - helping them reconn
 ect with themselves\, each other\, and the impact they are meant to make
 .&#160\;Whether she&#8217\;s leading a global conference\, guiding a tra
 nsformative conversation\, or delivering a keynote on bold self-reclamat
 ion\, Kiesha shows up as both mirror and spark - reflecting brilliance\,
  amplifying truth\, and activating the cultural catalysts within us all.
 </p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
