DESCRIPTION:Calling local artists who are interested in Public Art! Seat
 tle Office of Arts &amp\; Culture offers Public Art Boot Camp that is a 
 training and workshop program for artists ready to translate their skill
 s from studio art into the field of public art. Up to 18 individual arti
 sts will be selected to participate in this series of five workshops (an
 d paid to do so).<br><br>Are you a local studio artist who is interested
  in working within the field of public art\, but haven&#8217\;t had succ
 ess (or limited success) or don&#8217\;t know where to start? Public Art
  Boot Camp is program designed to provide an in-depth orientation and pr
 ovide building blocks and knowledge of the ins and outs of public art. S
 pace is limited in this series of 5 workshop training courses and so app
 ly today!<br><br>Thinking about applying to Public Art Boot Camp\, but h
 ave questions about the program or application process? Drop into the on
 line information session to hear directly from Project Managers about th
 e program and process.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
