X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Cost";ID=10963;TYPE=SingleLine:Free
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Detail image";ID=3052;TYPE=Image:<a href="htt
 ps://www.trumba.com/i/DgAYz08nsGYob38u%2AOkXGvL2.jpg" target="_blank" re
 l="noopener" title="https://www.trumba.com/i/DgAYz08nsGYob38u%2AOkXGvL2.
 jpg">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260310T094531Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Sound Me
 dicine for Liberation and Healing</em>\,&#160\;a series of sound medicin
 e offerings&#160\;hosted by Tory Trujillo.</strong><br><br>Now\, more th
 an ever\, we need opportunities to rest\, release grief and rage\, gathe
 r in safe space\, feel supported\, and give our nervous systems a chance
  to shift into the &#8220\;safe and connected mode.&quot\; Through this 
 series of sound medicine offerings\, artist Tory Trujillo supports our c
 ollective healing\, grounding\, and restoration.<br><br>Join us for six 
 sessions throughout 2026\, on the second Thursdays of March\, April\, Ma
 y\, October\, November\, and December.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Futur
 e</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installa
 tions\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed t
 o help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the D
 owntown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (2nd Thursdays)</strong>:</
 p><ul> <li>March 12	</li><li>April 9	</li><li>May 14	</li><li>October 8	
 </li><li>November 12	</li><li>December 10</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours 
 are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m.
  &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bio:</strong><br><a href="http
 s://www.torytrujillo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Tory T
 rujillo</strong></a> is a Two-Spirit\, Mixed-Blood Mexican Indigenous Fa
 cilitator of Healing and Professional Vocalist. Her Modalities include S
 ound Medicine\, Ritual\, Bodywork\, and Energy work. Her transformationa
 l sound medicine sessions are informed by her ancestral lineage and enha
 nced through additional training.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/194513421
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/arts/experience/arts-events?trumba
 Embed=view%3devent%26eventid%3d194513421
END:VEVENT
