DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for the&#160\;Mo
 bile Book Fair and Zine Library</strong><strong>\,&#160\;a series of pla
 za pop ups</strong> <strong> hosted by Common Area Maintenance.</strong>
 <br><br>Free zines\, books\, artist-made publications\, and participator
 y workshops furnish this book fair on the King Street Station plaza. Fea
 tured zines and printed works explore hope for the future through the le
 ns of secret histories and overlooked stories from Seattle&#8217\;s pock
 et neighborhoods.<br><br>Join us for six pop ups in 2026\, on the First 
 Thursdays of May through September.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</
 em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installatio
 ns\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed to h
 elp us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Down
 town core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (1st Thursdays &amp\; Summer S
 olstice)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>May 7	</li><li>June 4	</li><li>June 20&#1
 60\;&#8212\; LONGEST DAY	</li><li>July 2	</li><li>August 6	</li><li>Sept
 ember 3</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8
 211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong
 >Organizer bio:</strong><br><strong><a href="https://www.camseattle.org/
 " target="_blank" rel="noopener">Common AREA Maintenance</a></strong> (C
 AM) is an artist run organization rooted in the belief that creativity t
 hrives through shared space\, collective care\, and public participation
 . CAM supports a growing community of artists\, performers\, writers\, o
 rganizers\, and neighbors by providing accessible and affordable spaces 
 for experimentation\, dialogue\, and connection.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/194911111
