DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Setting 
 of the Daybreak Star</em></strong><strong>\,&#160\;a series of plaza con
 certs</strong> <strong> hosted by United Indians of All Tribes Foundatio
 n\, Daybreak Star Radio Network</strong><strong>. June features a perfor
 mance by Supaman!&#160\;</strong><br><br>This series of events on the Ki
 ng Street Station Plaza creates an urban sanctuary where participants ca
 n gather in celebration as the day transitions to evening. The programs&
 #160\;highlight Indigenous performers\, creating an accessible entry poi
 nt for communities to engage with Native music and&#160\;cultural tradit
 ions.<br><br>Join us for four sessions in 2026\, on the second Thursdays
  of June through September.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160
 \;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installations\, exh
 ibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed to help us d
 ream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Downtown cor
 e.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (2nd Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>
 June 11&#160\;&#8212\; Supaman	</li><li>July 9&#160\;&#8212\; Ribbon Ski
 rt	</li><li>August 13&#160\;&#8212\; The Neighborhood Kids	</li><li>Sept
 ember 10&#160\;&#8212\; TBA!</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#82
 11\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:0
 0 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bio:</strong><br>As a member of the &#8220
 \;Apsaalooke Nation&#8221\;\, <a href="https://www.supamanhiphop.net/abou
 t" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Supaman</strong></a> makes his
  home on Aps&#225\;alooke lands in Montana. &#8220\;Supaman&#8221\; Is C
 hristian Takes Gun Parrish\, a Native American dancer and innovative hip
  hop artist who has dedicated his life to empowering and spreading a mes
 sage of hope\, pride and resilience through his original art form. He ha
 s been the recipient of the 2017 MTV VMA award for &#8220\;Best Fight Ag
 ainst the System&#8221\;! He is also a Nammy &#8220\;Native American Mus
 ic Award&#8221\; winner\, &#8220\;North American Indigenous Image Award 
 winner\, and &#160\;7 &#8220\;Tunney Award winner. He was awarded &#160
 \;The Aboriginal Peoples Choice Music Award in Canada for best video and 
 was voted MTV&#8217\;s new Artist of the Week! His nominations brought h
 im home awards for Best Hip Hop Album and Best Producer for the Indigeno
 us Music Awards. His videos have received millions of views on youtube a
 nd facebook which has put him in high demand touring extensively through
 out the U.S.A and internationally. He has performed for Google at the Go
 ogle headquarters in San Francisco. He recently was asked to audition fo
 r America&#8217\;s Got Talent and the Broadway play Hamilton. He is curr
 ently on tour around the country spreading the good medicine of resilien
 cy\, love\, laughter and inclusion.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</stron
 g><br><a href="https://unitedindians.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener
 "><strong>Daybreak Star Radio</strong></a> is<strong>&#160\;</strong>a N
 ative American radio station with a sacred mission to Indigenize the air
 waves. Their&#160\;team is 100% Native American\, with every staff membe
 r actively engaged in their tribal communities. Their managers bring div
 erse creative backgrounds as artists\, theatre workers\, and musicians\,
  infusing programming with authentic cultural perspectives. The station 
 serves as a vital cultural hub for Native American\, First Nations\, and
  Pacific Islander communities\,&#160\;showcasing Indigenous artists and 
 voices that are typically underrepresented in mainstream media. This com
 mitment stems from their deep connections to our heritage and ancestral 
 knowledge systems.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
