DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for the&#160\;Mo
 bile Book Fair and Zine Library</strong><strong>\,&#160\;a series of pla
 za pop ups</strong> <strong> hosted by Common Area Maintenance.</strong>
 <br><br>Free zines\, books\, artist-made publications\, and participator
 y workshops furnish this book fair on the King Street Station plaza. Fea
 tured zines and printed works explore hope for the future through the le
 ns of secret histories and overlooked stories from Seattle&#8217\;s pock
 et neighborhoods.<br><br>Join us for six pop ups in 2026\, on the First 
 Thursdays of May through September.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future <
 /em>is&#160\;a series of public art activations\, installations\, exhibi
 tions\, and performances throughout the Downtown core\, including in the
  Chinatown-International District\, Pioneer Square\, Stadium District\, 
 and around Union Station and King Street Station.<br><br><strong>SERIES 
 SCHEDULE (1st Thursdays &amp\; Summer Solstice)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>Ma
 y 7	</li><li>June 4	</li><li>June 20&#160\;&#8212\; LONGEST DAY	</li><li
 >July 2	</li><li>August 6	</li><li>September 3</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery h
 ours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11
  a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</strong><br><stro
 ng><a href="https://www.camseattle.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
 Common AREA Maintenance</a></strong> (CAM) is an artist run organization
  rooted in the belief that creativity thrives through shared space\, col
 lective care\, and public participation. CAM supports a growing communit
 y of artists\, performers\, writers\, organizers\, and neighbors by prov
 iding accessible and affordable spaces for experimentation\, dialogue\, 
 and connection.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
