DTSTAMP:20260408T125237Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>The Livi
 ng Legacy of Joe Brazil</em></strong><strong>\,&#160\;a series of plaza 
 concerts</strong> <strong> hosted by Joe Brazil Legacy.</strong><br><br>
 A tribute to the enduring vision and impact of legendary jazz musician\,
  educator\, and community builder Joe Brazil\, this concert series remem
 bers a giant whose shoulders we stand upon to build our future\, featuri
 ng live music and dance on the King Street Station plaza.<br><br>Join us
  for four concerts in 2026\, on the First Thursdays of June through Sept
 ember.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series o
 f free public art activations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performanc
 es\, and learning experiences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and gr
 ow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SER
 IES SCHEDULE (1st Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>June 4&#160\;&#8212\;
  Joe Brazil Legacy Tribute + Joe Brazil Legacy House Band	</li><li>July 
 2&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;&#8220\;Blues Man&#8221\; Johnny Moore +&#160\;CT
  Thompson	</li><li>August 6 &#8212\;&#160\;The Magic of Makini + Phyllis
  Talley	</li><li>September 3&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;Lonnie Williams Then &
 amp\; Now + Medearis Dixson</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#821
 1\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00
  p.m.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</strong><br><strong><a href="https:/
 /joebrazil.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Joe Brazil Legacy</a></s
 trong> is built on years of hands-on experience producing deeply rooted
 \, intergenerational community events. These gatherings have become belov
 ed cultural touchstones in our community\, known not just for live music
 \, but for fostering connection\, pride\, and purpose across generations
 .</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
