 wide\,Pioneer Square
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact";ID=10948;TYPE=SingleLine:Rana San
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact Phone";ID=10950;TYPE=PhoneUS:(206) 25
 6-6279
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact Email";ID=10949;TYPE=Email:<a href="m
 ailto:Rana.San@seattle.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rana.San@seat
 tle.gov</a>
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Audience";ID=10952;TYPE=CustomAsset:All
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Pre-Register";ID=10961;TYPE=Boolean:No
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Cost";ID=10963;TYPE=SingleLine:Free
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Detail image";ID=3052;TYPE=Image:<a href="htt
 ps://www.trumba.com/i/DgCAJj9LrF%2AXSqZ3j04ccshA.png" target="_blank" re
 l="noopener" title="https://www.trumba.com/i/DgCAJj9LrF%2AXSqZ3j04ccshA.
 png">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260304T131231Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>The Drea
 ming Room: Soundscapes for Deep Rest</em>\,</strong> <strong>a concert s
 eries&#160\;hosted by Stephanie Ann Ball.</strong><br><br>This community
 -rooted concert series is designed to support nervous system recovery\, 
 emotional release\, and collective connections through sound meditation
 \, music\, and storytelling. Come rest and connect over the course of thi
 s renewing series\, every other month on the third Thursday&#160\;betwee
 n February and December.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;i
 s&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installations\, exhibi
 tions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed to help us drea
 m\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Downtown core.<
 br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (3rd Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>Feb
 ruary 19&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;rejuvenation + renewal	</li><li>April 16&#
 160\;&#8212\;&#160\;creativity\, fun\, expansion	</li><li>June 18&#160\;
 &#8212\;&#160\;joyful\, wondrous playtime	</li><li>August 20&#160\;&#821
 2\;&#160\;transitioning	</li><li>October 15&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;gratitu
 de + reflection	</li><li>December 17&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;celebration + 
 releasing</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &
 #8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><stro
 ng>Artist bio:<br><a href="https://stephanieannball.com/" target="_blank
 " rel="noopener">Stephanie Ann Ball</a></strong> is&#160\;a healing arti
 st and sound meditation facilitator. Her work sits at the intersection o
 f therapeutic sound\, science\, and well-being. Using sound meditation\,
  energy work\, and subconscious reprogramming techniques\, Stephanie hel
 ps individuals and teams regulate the nervous system\, release stress\, 
 and access states of calm\, clarity\, and flow. The best part? It all st
 arts with something easy and fun&#8212\;listening to music.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/194911611
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/arts/experience/arts-events?trumba
 Embed=view%3devent%26eventid%3d194911611
END:VEVENT
