DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Setting 
 of the Daybreak Star</em></strong><strong>\,&#160\;a series of plaza con
 certs</strong> <strong> hosted by United Indians of All Tribes Foundatio
 n\, Daybreak Star Radio Network</strong><strong>.</strong><br><br>This s
 eries of events on the King Street Station Plaza creates an urban sanctu
 ary where participants can gather in celebration as the day transitions 
 to evening. The programs&#160\;highlight Indigenous performers\, creatin
 g an accessible entry point for communities to engage with Native music 
 and&#160\;cultural traditions.<br><br>Join us for four sessions in 2026
 \, on the second Thursdays of June through September.<br><br>We Still Dre
 am a Future&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, ins
 tallations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences desig
 ned to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout 
 the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (2nd Thursdays):</stro
 ng></p><ul> <li>June 11&#160\;&#8212\; Supaman	</li><li>July 9&#160\;&#8
 212\; Ribbon Skirt	</li><li>August 13&#160\;&#8212\; The Neighborhood Ki
 ds	</li><li>September 10&#160\;&#8212\; TBA!</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hou
 rs are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a
 .m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</strong><br><a href
 ="https://unitedindians.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Day
 break Star Radio</strong></a> is<strong>&#160\;</strong>a Native America
 n radio station with a sacred mission to Indigenize the airwaves. Their&
 #160\;team is 100% Native American\, with every staff member actively en
 gaged in their tribal communities. Their managers bring diverse creative
  backgrounds as artists\, theatre workers\, and musicians\, infusing pro
 gramming with authentic cultural perspectives. The station serves as a v
 ital cultural hub for Native American\, First Nations\, and Pacific Isla
 nder communities\,&#160\;showcasing Indigenous artists and voices that a
 re typically underrepresented in mainstream media. This commitment stems
  from their deep connections to our heritage and ancestral knowledge sys
 tems.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
