DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Grief Ri
 tuals</em>\,</strong> <strong>a ritual performance&#160\;by Little Brown
  Language</strong><strong>.</strong><br><br><em>Grief Rituals</em> explo
 res hidden histories of migration\, ancestral memory and loss\, using ri
 tual performance as a medium for supporting communal experiences of grie
 ving and the forms of solidarity which may emerge. Collaborating across 
 art forms\, artists make space for collective grief and healing.<br><br>
 <em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public 
 art activations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learn
 ing experiences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking pl
 ace&#160\;throughout the Downtown core.</p><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed.
  &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211
 \; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bio:<br><a href="https://www.naomibrag
 in.com/lbl-projects" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Little Brown Languag
 e</a></strong> (LBL) is a performance collaborative based in Seattle who
  build new forms of solidarity among artist-organizers by activating loc
 al communities through embodied cultural practice. They believe in the p
 ower of small-scale solidarities to fluidly adapt to our communities&#82
 17\; changing needs in an uncertain sociopolitical climate. LBL emphasiz
 es ritual as dreamwork that activates portals to access ancestral memori
 es of our bio and chosen family lines.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
