DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Sound Me
 dicine for Liberation and Healing</em>\,&#160\;a series of sound medicin
 e offerings&#160\;hosted by Tory Trujillo.</strong><br><br>Now\, more th
 an ever\, we need opportunities to rest\, release grief and rage\, gathe
 r in safe space\, feel supported\, and give our nervous systems a chance
  to shift into the &#8220\;safe and connected mode.&quot\; Through this 
 series of sound medicine offerings\, artist Tory Trujillo supports our c
 ollective healing\, grounding\, and restoration.<br><br>Join us for six 
 sessions throughout 2026\, on the second Thursdays of March\, April\, Ma
 y\, October\, November\, and December.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Futur
 e </em>is&#160\;a series of public art activations\, installations\, exh
 ibitions\, and performances throughout the Downtown core\, including in 
 the Chinatown-International District\, Pioneer Square\, Stadium District
 \, and around Union Station and King Street Station.<br><br><strong>SERI
 ES SCHEDULE (2nd Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>March 12	</li><li>Apri
 l 9	</li><li>May 14	</li><li>October 8	</li><li>November 12	</li><li>Dec
 ember 10</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#
 8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><stron
 g>Artist bio:</strong><br><a href="https://www.torytrujillo.com/" target
 ="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Tory Trujillo</strong></a> is a Two-Spi
 rit\, Mixed-Blood Mexican Indigenous Facilitator of Healing and Professi
 onal Vocalist. Her Modalities include Sound Medicine\, Ritual\, Bodywork
 \, and Energy work. Her transformational sound medicine sessions are inf
 ormed by her ancestral lineage and enhanced through additional training.
 </p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
