DTSTAMP:20260223T101211Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Songs of
  Defiance and Sisterhood</em>\,</strong> <strong>a concert and artist ta
 lk by Mahsa and Marjan Vahdat</strong><strong>.</strong><br><br><em>Song
 s of Defiance and Sisterhood</em> is a musical and narrative journey sha
 ped by poetry\, resilience\, and the enduring power of artistic expressi
 on in the face of adversity. Iranian vocalists and cultural activists Ma
 hsa and Marjan Vahdat create a shared space for connection and hope thro
 ugh music\, poetry\, and an artist talk back.<br><br><em>We Still Dream 
 a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, i
 nstallations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences des
 igned to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughou
 t the Downtown core.</p><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a
 .m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br>
 <strong>Artist bio:</strong><br><strong><a href="https://www.mahsavahdat
 .net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mahsa and Marjan Vahdat</a>&#160\;
 </strong>are&#160\;Iranian vocalists and composers with deep roots in Pe
 rsian classical and regional music. Over the past three decades\, they h
 ave developed a distinct musical language rooted in traditional and regi
 onal Iranian music and poetry and their personal experience as women who
  defied bans imposed by Authorities after the Islamic Revolution\, and n
 ow shaping their music while we are in exile. They are part of an intern
 ational artistic community committed to cultural dialogue\, freedom of e
 xpression\, and the preservation and renewal of musical traditions. Thei
 r work reflects the resilience of Iranian women\, the strength of oral t
 raditions\, and the power of the human voice to carry memory\, identity
 \, and collective experience.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
